5 minutes ago, legs said:

Hello,

I have downloaded the mod and checked version compatibility and everything seems in order. I had the model rework that i deleted because the mod did not seem to work.

I made a test vehicle consisting in command pod, batteries (the 4000 capacity ones) and an unobstructed piston.

I tried using the command panel and the key binding to make it move but i did not succeeded. The EC draw of the psiton is null even when ordering movement and the arrow activity sign is showing up.

What can i do ?

thank you in advance 

Have you tried other parts? Can you post a screenshot of the craft and your log?
With 2.0.3, I'm getting some NRE spam when launching stuff - funny things is I don't think I even have any IR parts on the craft: https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/59567837/output_log_IRNRE.txt

Can you test with IR enabled craft?

@AccidentalDisassembly, could you please redownload release from github and test again.

Edited May 11, 2016 by Ziw

Will try the release download again here.

 

EDIT: But if you're referring to the GitHub 2.0.3 Core files, that's what I've got in my GameData right now (I hope) and I don't see any new changes to it in the last 4 hours...

Is it possible to create motors that can be moved freely, but will move when power is applied, and you can also force it to lock. Basically like a car wheel.
